explanation: This solution first creates a set of all uppercase letters in the string. Then, it iterates over the string again to find the greatest letter that appears in both lowercase and uppercase. If such a letter is found, it is returned in uppercase. If no such letter is found, an empty string is returned. The efficiency is high because the solution uses a set to store the uppercase letters, which has an average time complexity of O(1) for insertion and lookup.

